# SecureZ+ OS — Tor Configuration
# /etc/tor/torrc
#
# Transparent proxy mode: routes ALL system traffic through Tor.
# Enabled only when user opts in (not default).

## Transparent proxy settings
TransPort 9040
DNSPort 5353

## SOCKS proxy for applications that support it
SocksPort 9050

## Logging (minimal — we don't log traffic)
Log notice syslog

## Security hardening
Sandbox 1
SafeLogging 1

## Country/exit node preferences (uncomment to customize)
# ExitNodes {us},{gb},{de},{nl},{ch}
# StrictNodes 1

## Bridge support (for censored networks)
# UseBridges 1
# Bridge obfs4 <bridge-line>
# ClientTransportPlugin obfs4 exec /usr/bin/obfs4proxy
